The 27Al hemispherical aluminum target of thickness
3-mm and diameter 40-mm.
Five EJ301(5 x 5)-cm2 liquid scintillator
detectors, placed at a distance of 2.0 m for angle 0,
30, 60 degree and at 1.5 m for 90, 120 degree.
To measure neutrons spectra.
To separate neutrons from gamma-ray photons.
Statistical
The background corrections for the removal of the
scattered components were carried out using the
shadow bar technique.
For this two 30-cm-long cylindrical bars, one made of
iron and the other made of high-density polyethylene,
placed end to end between the target and the
detector.
The background spectrum when subtracted from the total
experimental spectrum at that angle produces the net
neutron distribution due to heavy-ion nuclear reaction.
